DISCERNMENT Performance	EduSavvy teachers periodically review chat logs to evaluate: Is Hesabu Coach behaving as configured? Per Tsavo: 'Performance Discernment — is the AI's behavior helping the team or causing confusion?' If the Ranger is accidentally solving problems instead of guiding, behavioral reconfiguration is required.
Temperature Setting: LOW (0.1)	VERY LOW temperature: In Agency mode, unpredictable responses are dangerous — a student could receive incorrect algebra guidance with no human present to correct it. Tsavo: 'For safety-critical tasks, use a lower temperature setting to produce more predictable and focused responses.' Low temp ensures consistent Socratic scaffolding every session.
RAG Integration	RAG connects Hesabu Coach to the KICD CBC Mathematics syllabus document and current Nairobi market pricing data (maize prices, M-Pesa fee schedules). This prevents the Ranger from generating math problems with outdated fees or incorrect CBC scope. Per Tsavo: RAG 'connects AI to live data sources, banishing mirages that could lead your pride into swamps.'
Negative Prompt	"Do not solve problems directly for the student. Do not reference currency or pricing outside Kenya/Uganda. Do not use non-EA sporting statistics as math examples." This prevents the Western-centric failure mode of the original prompt.

INTERACTION C  |  Parent Progress Report — Diligence Protocol

Original prompt (failed): "Summarize my child's performance."  →  Risk: AI hallucinates national percentiles, fabricates comparisons, no transparency about AI role.

REDESIGNED PROMPT WITH DILIGENCE FRAMEWORK:
Generate a parent progress report for student: [STUDENT_NAME], Class [FORM], Term [X].

USE ONLY the following verified data from EduSavvy's internal quiz database:
    • Quiz scores: [INSERT ACTUAL SCORES FROM DATABASE — DO NOT INFER]
    • Attendance record: [INSERT ACTUAL ATTENDANCE — DO NOT INFER]
    • Teacher comment flags: [INSERT TEACHER NOTES IF ANY]

FORMAT — The report must:
    • Open with: 'This report was generated with AI assistance and reviewed by [Teacher Name] before sharing.'
    • Use only EduSavvy internal quiz averages for comparison — never national or regional percentiles
    • Use strength-first framing: 'Your child shows strong effort in... and is developing skills in...'
    • Flag any claim that cannot be verified against actual quiz data with: [TEACHER TO VERIFY]
    • Close with one specific, actionable recommendation (e.g., 'Practice 2 algebra problems per day using M-Pesa budgeting scenarios')

BIAS AWARENESS CHECK — Before generating:
    • Do not use language that implies the student's challenges are due to family background or socioeconomic status
    • Do not compare performance across gender lines
    • Do not use deficit language (e.g., 'failing,' 'weak,' 'behind')

NEGATIVE PROMPT: Do not generate national ranking percentiles, regional comparisons, or any benchmark data that EduSavvy does not hold in its own database. Do not state or imply that this report was written by a human teacher without disclosure.

